Also, keep in mind that running large models like GPT-2 on a mobile device might not be feasible due to resource constraints, such as CPU, memory, and power. Generally, for mobile deployment, you should use smaller and more optimized models. If running the model on-device turns out to be impractical, you might need to consider an alternative approach where your app would send a request to a server that runs the model and then sends back the response.

